rdfs:Class.rdfs:comment: Aggregates three properties defined in RFC2426. Originally all three were attached directly to a person. One person could have only one title and one role within one organization. This class is intended to lift this limitation.
rdfs:Class.rdfs:label: Affiliation

rdf:Property.rdfs:comment: Department. The organizational unit within the organization.
rdf:Property.rdfs:label: department

rdf:Property.rdfs:comment: Name of an organization or a unit within an organization the object represented by a Contact is associated with. An equivalent of the 'ORG' property defined in RFC 2426 Sec. 3.5.5
rdf:Property.rdfs:label: org

rdfs:Class.rdfs:comment: Predefined instances to indicate the auth status: yes, no, requested
rdfs:Class.rdfs:label: IM Address approval status

rdfs:Class.rdfs:comment: A Bulletin Board System (BBS) phone number. Inspired by the (TYPE=bbsl) parameter of the TEL property as defined in RFC 2426 sec 3.3.1.
rdfs:Class.rdfs:label: BbsNumber

rdfs:Class.rdfs:comment: A car phone number. Inspired by the (TYPE=car) parameter of the TEL property as defined in RFC 2426 sec 3.3.1.
rdfs:Class.rdfs:label: CarPhoneNumber

rdfs:Class.rdfs:comment: A cellular phone number. Inspired by the (TYPE=cell) parameter of the TEL property as defined in RFC 2426 sec 3.3.1. Usually a cellular phone can accept voice calls as well as textual messages (SMS), therefore this class has two superclasses.
rdfs:Class.rdfs:label: CellPhoneNumber

rdfs:Class.rdfs:comment: A Contact. A piece of data that can provide means to identify or communicate with an entity.
rdfs:Class.rdfs:label: Contact

rdf:Property.rdfs:comment: An encryption key attached to a contact. Inspired by the KEY property defined in RFC 2426 sec. 3.7.2
rdf:Property.rdfs:label: key

rdf:Property.rdfs:comment: A value that represents a globally unique identifier corresponding to the individual or resource associated with the Contact. An equivalent of the 'UID' property defined in RFC 2426 Sec. 3.6.7
rdf:Property.rdfs:label: contactUID

rdf:Property.rdfs:comment: Unique ID for the contact in the local storage
rdf:Property.rdfs:label: local contact UID

rdf:Property.rdfs:comment: Geographical location of the contact. Inspired by the 'GEO' property specified in RFC 2426 Sec. 3.4.2
rdf:Property.rdfs:label: hasLocation

rdf:Property.rdfs:comment: A nickname of the Object represented by this Contact. This is an equivalen of the 'NICKNAME' property as defined in RFC 2426 Sec. 3.1.3.
rdf:Property.rdfs:label: nickname

rdf:Property.rdfs:comment: A note about the object represented by this Contact. An equivalent for the 'NOTE' property defined in RFC 2426 Sec. 3.6.2
rdf:Property.rdfs:label: note

rdf:Property.rdfs:comment: An object that represent an object represented by this Contact. Usually this property is used to link a Contact to an organization, to a contact to the representative of this organization the user directly interacts with. An equivalent for the 'AGENT' property defined in RFC 2426 Sec. 3.5.4
rdf:Property.rdfs:label: representative

rdf:Property.rdfs:comment: To specify the formatted text corresponding to the name of the object the Contact represents. An equivalent of the FN property as defined in RFC 2426 Sec. 3.1.1.
rdf:Property.rdfs:label: fullname

rdf:Property.rdfs:comment: Photograph attached to a Contact. The DataObject refered to by this property is usually interpreted as an nfo:Image. Inspired by the PHOTO property defined in RFC 2426 sec. 3.1.4
rdf:Property.rdfs:label: photo

rdf:Property.rdfs:comment: Birth date of the object represented by this Contact. An equivalent of the 'BDAY' property as defined in RFC 2426 Sec. 3.1.5.
rdf:Property.rdfs:label: birthDate

rdf:Property.rdfs:comment: Links a Contact with a ContactGroup it belongs to.
rdf:Property.rdfs:label: addressLocation

rdf:Property.rdfs:comment: Sound clip attached to a Contact. The DataObject refered to by this property is usually interpreted as an nfo:Audio. Inspired by the SOUND property defined in RFC 2425 sec. 3.6.6.
rdf:Property.rdfs:label: sound

rdf:Property.rdfs:comment: links a contact with the calendar event of his birthday. (NCAL version)
rdf:Property.rdfs:label: birthday event

rdf:Property.rdfs:comment: links a contact with the calendar event of an anniversary. (NCAL version)
rdf:Property.rdfs:label: anniversary event

rdf:Property.rdfs:comment: links a contact with the calendar event of his birthday. (SCAL version)
rdf:Property.rdfs:label: birthday event

rdf:Property.rdfs:comment: links a contact with the calendar event of an anniversary. (SCAL version)
rdf:Property.rdfs:label: anniversary event

rdfs:Class.rdfs:comment: A group of Contacts. Could be used to express a group in an addressbook or on a contact list of an IM application. One contact can belong to many groups.
rdfs:Class.rdfs:label: ContactGroup

rdf:Property.rdfs:comment: The name of the contact group. This property was NOT defined in the VCARD standard. See documentation of the 'ContactGroup' class for details
rdf:Property.rdfs:label: contactGroupName

rdf:Property.rdfs:comment: Audio file linked with a contact group
rdf:Property.rdfs:label: Audio ringtone

rdf:Property.rdfs:comment: Video file linked with a contact group
rdf:Property.rdfs:label: Video ringtone

rdf:Property.rdfs:comment: File linked with a contact group to vibrate on a pleasant frequency
rdf:Property.rdfs:label: Vibration ringtone

rdfs:Class.rdfs:comment: A contact list, this class represents an addressbook or a contact list of an IM application. Contacts inside a contact list can belong to contact groups.
rdfs:Class.rdfs:label: ContactList

rdf:Property.rdfs:comment: A property used to group contacts into contact groups. This property was NOT defined in the VCARD standard. See documentation for the 'ContactList' class for details
rdf:Property.rdfs:label: containsContact

rdfs:Class.rdfs:comment: An entity occuring on a contact list (usually interpreted as an nco:Contact)
rdfs:Class.rdfs:label: ContactListDataObject

rdfs:Class.rdfs:comment: A superclass for all contact media - ways to contact an entity represented by a Contact instance. Some of the subclasses of this class (the various kinds of telephone numbers and postal addresses) have been inspired by the values of the TYPE parameter of ADR and TEL properties defined in RFC 2426 sec. 3.2.1. and 3.3.1 respectively. Each value is represented by an appropriate subclass with two major exceptions TYPE=home and TYPE=work. They are to be expressed by the roles these contact media are attached to i.e. contact media with TYPE=home parameter are to be attached to the default role (nco:Contact or nco:PersonContact), whereas media with TYPE=work parameter should be attached to nco:Affiliation or nco:OrganizationContact.
rdfs:Class.rdfs:label: ContactMedium

rdf:Property.rdfs:comment: A comment about the contact medium.
rdf:Property.rdfs:label: contactMediumComment

rdfs:Class.rdfs:comment: Domestic Delivery Addresse. Class inspired by TYPE=dom parameter of the ADR property defined in RFC 2426 sec. 3.2.1
rdfs:Class.rdfs:label: DomesticDeliveryAddress

rdfs:Class.rdfs:comment: An email address. The recommended best practice is to use mailto: uris for instances of this class.
rdfs:Class.rdfs:label: EmailAddress

rdfs:Class.rdfs:comment: A fax number. Inspired by the (TYPE=fax) parameter of the TEL property as defined in RFC 2426 sec 3.3.1.
rdfs:Class.rdfs:label: FaxNumber

rdfs:Class.rdfs:comment: Gender. Instances of this class may include male and female.
rdfs:Class.rdfs:label: Gender

rdfs:Class.rdfs:comment: An account in an Instant Messaging system. This refers to IM accounts of the user 'me'.
rdfs:Class.rdfs:label: IMAccount

rdf:Property.rdfs:comment: Indicates that this Instant Messaging account has the specified Instant Messaging address in the contact list.
rdf:Property.rdfs:label: hasIMAccount

rdf:Property.rdfs:comment: Instant Messaging address of this IM account. The user 'me' can send and receive messages from this IM address.
rdf:Property.rdfs:label: imAccountAddress

rdf:Property.rdfs:comment: Type of the IM account. This may be the name of the service that provides the IM functionality. Examples might include Jabber, ICQ, MSN etc
rdf:Property.rdfs:label: imAccountType

rdf:Property.rdfs:comment: The user-visible name of this account. This SHOULD be chosen by the user at account creation time. The account creation user interface is responsible for setting a reasonable default value in the user's locale; something like 'Jabber (bob@example.com)' would be sensible.
rdf:Property.rdfs:label: displayname

rdf:Property.rdfs:comment: The picture the user wants to show to others in this account. This has been replaced by nco:imAvatar.
rdf:Property.rdfs:label: account avatar

rdfs:Class.rdfs:comment: An instant messaging address such as xmpp:foo@bar.com.
rdfs:Class.rdfs:label: IM Address

rdf:Property.rdfs:comment: Identifier of the IM account. Examples of such identifier might include ICQ UINs, Jabber IDs, Skype names etc.
rdf:Property.rdfs:label: imID

rdf:Property.rdfs:comment: A nickname attached to a particular IM address.
rdf:Property.rdfs:label: imNickname

rdf:Property.rdfs:comment: A picture attached to a particular IM address.
rdf:Property.rdfs:label: imAvatar

rdf:Property.rdfs:comment: Protocol of the account ('skype', 'gtalk', 'icq', ...)
rdf:Property.rdfs:label: imProtocol

rdf:Property.rdfs:comment: A feature common in most IM systems. A message left by the user for all his/her contacts to see.
rdf:Property.rdfs:label: imStatusMessage

rdf:Property.rdfs:comment: Timestamp of the last change in the presence status
rdf:Property.rdfs:label: Presence last modified

rdf:Property.rdfs:comment: Capabilities of an IM Contact, what can we interact with him
rdf:Property.rdfs:label: imContact Capability

rdf:Property.rdfs:comment: Has the other end authorize to receive information about his changes
rdf:Property.rdfs:label: IM Address authorization status in the remote end

rdf:Property.rdfs:comment: Do i authorize this im Account to receive my information
rdf:Property.rdfs:label: IM Address authorization status in the local end

rdfs:Class.rdfs:comment: Features of a certain IM connection (depends on the IMAccount implementation used by the Contact)
rdfs:Class.rdfs:label: IM Capabilities

rdfs:Class.rdfs:comment: Contact coming from an IM Account. This has been deprecated in favor of using nco:PersonContact with nco:hasIMAddress.
rdfs:Class.rdfs:label: IM Contact

rdf:Property.rdfs:comment: Indicates that an Instant Messaging account owned by an entity represented by this contact. This has been replaced by nco:fromIMAccount.
rdf:Property.rdfs:label: hasIMAccount

rdf:Property.rdfs:comment: ID of the contact in the service like my.friend@xmail.com. This has been replaced by nco:imId.
rdf:Property.rdfs:label: imContactId

rdf:Property.rdfs:comment: Visible nickname of the user in a service. This has been replaced by nco:imNickname.
rdf:Property.rdfs:label: imContactNickname

rdf:Property.rdfs:comment: Status message of the user in a service. This has been replaced by nco:imStatusMessage.
rdf:Property.rdfs:label: imContactStatusMessage

rdf:Property.rdfs:comment: Online availability of the user in a service. This has been replaced by nco:imPresence.
rdf:Property.rdfs:label: imContactPresence

rdf:Property.rdfs:comment: Capabilities of an IM Contact, what can we interact with him. This has been replaced by nco:imCapability.
rdf:Property.rdfs:label: imContact Capability

rdfs:Class.rdfs:comment: International Delivery Addresse. Class inspired by TYPE=intl parameter of the ADR property defined in RFC 2426 sec. 3.2.1
rdfs:Class.rdfs:label: InternationalDeliveryAddress

rdfs:Class.rdfs:comment: An ISDN phone number. Inspired by the (TYPE=isdn) parameter of the TEL property as defined in RFC 2426 sec 3.3.1.
rdfs:Class.rdfs:label: IsdnNumber

rdfs:Class.rdfs:comment: A number that can accept textual messages.
rdfs:Class.rdfs:label: MessagingNumber

rdfs:Class.rdfs:comment: A metacontact groups PersonContacts and IMContacts coming from different sources, indicating that are the same entity in the real world. This has been deprecated in favor of merged contacts. Linking multiple contacts to a single person without merging is the task of pimo:Person and pimo:groundingOccurrence.
rdfs:Class.rdfs:label: MetaContact

rdfs:Class.rdfs:comment: A modem phone number. Inspired by the (TYPE=modem) parameter of the TEL property as defined in RFC 2426 sec 3.3.1.
rdfs:Class.rdfs:label: ModemNumber

rdfs:Class.rdfs:comment: A Contact that denotes on Organization.
rdfs:Class.rdfs:label: OrganizationContact

rdf:Property.rdfs:comment: Logo of a company. Inspired by the LOGO property defined in RFC 2426 sec. 3.5.3
rdf:Property.rdfs:label: logo

rdfs:Class.rdfs:comment: A pager phone number. Inspired by the (TYPE=pager) parameter of the TEL property as defined in RFC 2426 sec 3.3.1.
rdfs:Class.rdfs:label: PagerNumber

rdfs:Class.rdfs:comment: Parcel Delivery Addresse. Class inspired by TYPE=parcel parameter of the ADR property defined in RFC 2426 sec. 3.2.1
rdfs:Class.rdfs:label: ParcelDeliveryAddress

rdfs:Class.rdfs:comment: Personal Communication Services Number. A class inspired by the TYPE=pcs parameter of the TEL property defined in RFC 2426 sec. 3.3.1
rdfs:Class.rdfs:label: PcsNumber

rdfs:Class.rdfs:comment: A Contact that denotes a Person. A person can have multiple Affiliations.
rdfs:Class.rdfs:label: PersonContact

rdf:Property.rdfs:comment: Link a single contact with a metacontact
rdf:Property.rdfs:label: metacontact

rdf:Property.rdfs:comment: A suffix for the name of the Object represented by the given object. See documentation for the 'nameFamily' for details.
rdf:Property.rdfs:label: nameHonorificSuffix

rdf:Property.rdfs:comment: The family name of an Object represented by this Contact. These applies to people that have more than one given name. The 'first' one is considered 'the' given name (see nameGiven) property. All additional ones are considered 'additional' names. The name inherited from parents is the 'family name'. e.g. For Dr. John Phil Paul Stevenson Jr. M.D. A.C.P. we have contact with: honorificPrefix: 'Dr.', nameGiven: 'John', nameAdditional: 'Phil', nameAdditional: 'Paul', nameFamily: 'Stevenson', honorificSuffix: 'Jr.', honorificSuffix: 'M.D.', honorificSuffix: 'A.C.P.'. These properties form an equivalent of the compound 'N' property as defined in RFC 2426 Sec. 3.1.2
rdf:Property.rdfs:label: nameFamily

rdf:Property.rdfs:comment: A prefix for the name of the object represented by this Contact. See documentation for the 'nameFamily' property for details.
rdf:Property.rdfs:label: nameHonorificPrefix

rdf:Property.rdfs:comment: Indicates that an Instant Messaging account owned by an entity represented by this contact.
rdf:Property.rdfs:label: hasIMAccount

rdf:Property.rdfs:comment: The given name for the object represented by this Contact. See documentation for 'nameFamily' property for details.
rdf:Property.rdfs:label: nameGiven

rdf:Property.rdfs:comment: Additional given name of an object represented by this contact. See documentation for 'nameFamily' property for details.
rdf:Property.rdfs:label: nameAdditional

rdf:Property.rdfs:comment: A hobby associated with a PersonContact. This property can be used to express hobbies and interests.
rdf:Property.rdfs:label: hobby

rdf:Property.rdfs:comment: Gender of the given contact.
rdf:Property.rdfs:label: gender

rdf:Property.rdfs:comment: Links a PersonContact with an Affiliation.
rdf:Property.rdfs:label: hasAffiliation

rdf:Property.rdfs:comment: Audio file linked with a contact
rdf:Property.rdfs:label: Audio ringtone

rdf:Property.rdfs:comment: Video file linked with a contact
rdf:Property.rdfs:label: Video ringtone

rdf:Property.rdfs:comment: File linked with a contact to vibrate on a pleasant frequency
rdf:Property.rdfs:label: Vibration ringtone

rdfs:Class.rdfs:comment: A telephone number.
rdfs:Class.rdfs:label: PhoneNumber

rdfs:Class.rdfs:comment: A postal address. A class aggregating the various parts of a value for the 'ADR' property as defined in RFC 2426 Sec. 3.2.1.
rdfs:Class.rdfs:label: PostalAddress

rdf:Property.rdfs:comment: Region. Inspired by the fifth part of the value of the 'ADR' property as defined in RFC 2426, sec. 3.2.1
rdf:Property.rdfs:label: region

rdf:Property.rdfs:comment: A part of an address specifying the country. Inspired by the seventh part of the value of the 'ADR' property as defined in RFC 2426, sec. 3.2.1
rdf:Property.rdfs:label: country

rdf:Property.rdfs:comment: An extended part of an address. This field might be used to express parts of an address that aren't include in the name of the Contact but also aren't part of the actual location. Usually the streed address and following fields are enough for a postal letter to arrive. Examples may include ('University of California Campus building 45', 'Sears Tower 34th floor' etc.) Inspired by the second part of the value of the 'ADR' property as defined in RFC 2426, sec. 3.2.1
rdf:Property.rdfs:label: extendedAddress

rdf:Property.rdfs:comment: The geographical location of a postal address.
rdf:Property.rdfs:label: addressLocation

rdf:Property.rdfs:comment: The streed address. Inspired by the third part of the value of the 'ADR' property as defined in RFC 2426, sec. 3.2.1
rdf:Property.rdfs:label: streetAddress

rdf:Property.rdfs:comment: Postal Code. Inspired by the sixth part of the value of the 'ADR' property as defined in RFC 2426, sec. 3.2.1
rdf:Property.rdfs:label: postalcode

rdf:Property.rdfs:comment: Locality or City. Inspired by the fourth part of the value of the 'ADR' property as defined in RFC 2426, sec. 3.2.1
rdf:Property.rdfs:label: locality

rdf:Property.rdfs:comment: Post office box. This is the first part of the value of the 'ADR' property as defined in RFC 2426, sec. 3.2.1
rdf:Property.rdfs:label: pobox

rdfs:Class.rdfs:comment: Predefined set of status level instances
rdfs:Class.rdfs:label: Presence statuses

rdfs:Class.rdfs:comment: A role played by a contact. Contacts that denote people, can have many roles (e.g. see the hasAffiliation property and Affiliation class). Contacts that denote Organizations or other Agents usually have one role. Each role can introduce additional contact media.
rdfs:Class.rdfs:label: Role

rdf:Property.rdfs:comment: A superProperty for all properties linking a Contact to an instance of a contact medium.
rdf:Property.rdfs:label: hasContactMedium

rdf:Property.rdfs:comment: A uniform resource locator associated with the given role of a Contact. Inspired by the 'URL' property defined in RFC 2426 Sec. 3.6.8.
rdf:Property.rdfs:label: url

rdf:Property.rdfs:comment: A number for telephony communication with the object represented by this Contact. An equivalent of the 'TEL' property defined in RFC 2426 Sec. 3.3.1
rdf:Property.rdfs:label: hasPhoneNumber

rdf:Property.rdfs:comment: A url of a website.
rdf:Property.rdfs:label: websiteUrl

rdf:Property.rdfs:comment: An address for electronic mail communication with the object specified by this contact. An equivalent of the 'EMAIL' property as defined in RFC 2426 Sec. 3.3.1.
rdf:Property.rdfs:label: hasEmailAddress

rdf:Property.rdfs:comment: The URL of the FOAF file.
rdf:Property.rdfs:label: foafUrl

rdf:Property.rdfs:comment: A Blog url.
rdf:Property.rdfs:label: blogUrl

rdf:Property.rdfs:comment: The default Address for a Contact. An equivalent of the 'ADR' property as defined in RFC 2426 Sec. 3.2.1.
rdf:Property.rdfs:label: hasPostalAddress

rdf:Property.rdfs:comment: An address for communication using instant messages with the object specified by this contact.
rdf:Property.rdfs:label: imAddress

rdf:Property.rdfs:comment: Video avatar of a contact. Note that is an icon/avatar, not a generic 'present in video' property
rdf:Property.rdfs:label: Contact video

rdfs:Class.rdfs:comment: A Video telephone number. A class inspired by the TYPE=video parameter of the TEL property defined in RFC 2426 sec. 3.3.1
rdfs:Class.rdfs:label: VideoTelephoneNumber

rdfs:Class.rdfs:comment: A telephone number with voice communication capabilities. Class inspired by the TYPE=voice parameter of the TEL property defined in RFC 2426 sec. 3.3.1
rdfs:Class.rdfs:label: VoicePhoneNumber

rdf:Property.rdfs:comment: Indicates if the given number accepts voice mail. (e.g. there is an answering machine). Inspired by TYPE=msg parameter of the TEL property defined in RFC 2426 sec. 3.3.1
rdf:Property.rdfs:label: voiceMail

rdf:Property.rdfs:comment: An entity responsible for making contributions to the content of the InformationElement.
rdf:Property.rdfs:label: contributor

rdf:Property.rdfs:comment: Creator of a data object, an entity primarily responsible for the creation of the content of the data object.
rdf:Property.rdfs:label: creator

rdf:Property.rdfs:comment: An entity responsible for making the InformationElement available.
rdf:Property.rdfs:label: publisher
